{{Infobox protected area | name = Bluestone State Park | iucn_category = III | iucn_ref = <ref name="IUCN1">{{cite web|title=Bluestone State Park|url=https://www.protectedplanet.net/bluestone-state-park|website=Protected Planet|publisher=IUCN|accessdate=30 April 2018}}</ref><ref name="IUCN2">{{cite web|title=Bluestone Lake State Park|url=https://www.protectedplanet.net/bluestone-lake-state-park|website=Protected Planet|publisher=IUCN|accessdate=30 April 2018}}</ref> <!-- images --> | photo = Bluestone Lake at Bluestone River.jpg | photo_caption = [[Bluestone Lake]] near the state park marina. <!-- map --> | map = USA West Virginia | map_image = | map_size = | map_caption = Location of Bluestone State Park in West Virginia | relief = 1 <!-- location --> | location = [[Summers County, West Virginia|Summers]], West Virginia, United States | nearest_city = | nearest_town = | coordinates = {{coord|37|37|04|N|80|56|19|W|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <!-- stats --> | length = | length_mi = | length_km = | width = | width_mi = | width_km = | area_acre = 2154 | area_ref = <ref name=WVSPFacilities>[http://www.wvstateparks.com/recreation/WVSP_facilities_grid.PDF West Virginia State Parks Facilities Grid, accessed March 29, 2008] {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5fHBFhmDs?url=http://www.wvstateparks.com/recreation/WVSP_facilities_grid.PDF |date=March 14, 2009 }}</ref> | elevation = {{convert|1742|ft|m|abbr=on}} | elevation_avg = | elevation_min = | elevation_max = | dimensions = | designation = <!-- dates & info --> | authorized = | created = | designated = | established = 1950<ref name="WPaNM">{{cite book|title=Where People and Nature Meet: A History of the West Virginia State Parks|publisher=Pictorial Histories Publishing Company|location=[[Charleston, West Virginia|Charleston]], [[West Virginia]]|date=April 1988|isbn=0-933126-91-3}}</ref> | named_for = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = | administrator = | operator = | owner = <!-- website, embedded --> | website = {{URL|https://wvstateparks.com/park/bluestone-state-park/}} | embedded = }} '''Bluestone State Park''' is a [[state park]] in [[Summers County, West Virginia]]. The {{convert|2154|acre|adj=on}}<ref name=WVSPFacilities /> park is located along the western shore of [[Bluestone Lake]], an impoundment of the [[New River (West Virginia)|New River]] built and managed by the [[U.S. Army Corps of Engineers]]. The park and lake are named after the [[Bluestone River]], that flows into the [[New River (Kanawha River)|New River]] at the park.
==Features==
* 26 cabins * Campground with 77 campsites (22 with electrical hookup) * Boating access * Marina with boat and canoe rental * Swimming pool * Picnic area
