{{Infobox book | name = Kubrick the Dog | image = Kubrick the Dog.jpg<!-- include the file, px and alt: [[File:Example.jpg|200px|alt=Cover]] --> | caption = | author = [[Sean Ellis]] | title_orig = <!-- if not in English --> | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = English | series = | subject = | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[G. Schirmer|Schirmer Books]] | pub_date = February 28, 2011 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print | pages = 148 pages | isbn = 3829605056 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Kubrick the Dog''''' is a 2011 non-fiction photography book by British director [[Sean Ellis]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Vogue Photog Sean Ellis' Book About His Best Friend: Kubrick the Dog|url=http://racked.com/archives/2010/10/18/vogue-photog-sean-ellis-book-about-his-best-friend-kubrick-the-dog.php|publisher=Racked|accessdate=13 December 2012}}</ref> The book was released on February 28, 2011 through [[G. Schirmer|Schirmer Books]] and focuses on the life of Ellis's dog Kubrick. ''Kubrick the Dog'' features several photos of Kubrick, a [[Hungarian Vizsla]] that Ellis adopted as a puppy in 1998, in several poses and with different people such as [[Stella McCartney]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Spicer|first=Kate|title=Dog days|url=http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/style/living/Emotions/article414621.ece|accessdate=13 December 2012|newspaper=The Sunday Times|date=17 October 2010}}</ref>
Ellis began working on the book in 2010 after Kubrick's death by [[canine lymphoma]] as a way of working through his grief over the dog's death.<ref>{{cite news|title=Modefotograf Sean Ellis Der Hund, dem die Models zu Füßen lagen|url=http://www.fr-online.de/panorama/der-hund--dem-die-models-zu-fuessen-lagen,1472782,4816188.html|accessdate=13 December 2012|newspaper=Frankfurter Rundschau|date=8 November 2010}}</ref>
==Reception== Critical reception for the book was mostly positive.<ref>{{cite news|title=Im eigenen Pelz|url=http://www.taz.de/!64499/|accessdate=13 December 2012|newspaper=die Tageszeitung|date=2011-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Bildband "Kubrick The Dog" : Der Hund und die Topmodels|url=http://www.rp-online.de/kultur/kunst/der-hund-und-die-topmodels-1.2002834|accessdate=13 December 2012|newspaper=Rheinische Post|date=3 November 2010}}</ref> [[Basler Zeitung]] gave an overall positive review, stating that although some of the photographs felt a little deliberate, the book was also stirring.<ref>{{cite news|title=Showtime für den Hund|url=http://bazonline.ch/kultur/buecher/Showtime-fuer-den-Hund-/story/14796332|accessdate=13 December 2012|newspaper=Basler Zeitung|date=2010-11-16}}</ref>
